    <!--
    ========================================================================
    PUÑUY APU - COMPLETE SLEEP TRACKER APPLICATION STRINGS
    PRODUCTION-READY INTERNATIONALIZATION WITH C++ PERFORMANCE ENGINE
    ========================================================================

    CRITICAL INFORMATION FOR TRANSLATORS:

    1. APPLICATION CONTEXT:
       - Puñuy Apu is a high-performance sleep tracking app using AI algorithms
       - "Puñuy Apu" means "Sleep Mountain" in Quechua (Andean indigenous language)
       - The app automatically detects sleep patterns through phone usage analysis
       - Emphasizes privacy: all data stays on device, never shared

    2. TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE:
       - C++ native engine for millisecond-precision sleep detection
       - Real-time analysis of user interaction patterns
       - Machine learning capabilities for pattern recognition
       - Zero network transmission - complete privacy

    3. TONE GUIDELINES (MAINTAIN CONSISTENTLY):
       - Warm, encouraging, supportive (like a caring friend)
       - Health-focused but never medical/clinical
       - Personal and friendly, avoid corporate language
       - Celebrating good sleep, understanding about challenges
       - Privacy-first messaging (build trust)
       - Performance-focused (emphasize speed and efficiency)

    4. PLACEHOLDER FORMATS (NEVER TRANSLATE THESE):
       - %s = string replacement (times, text, names)
       - %d = number replacement (counts, durations, percentages)
       - %1$s, %2$s, %3$s = multiple ordered string replacements
       - %1$d, %2$d = multiple ordered number replacements
       - %.1f, %.2f = decimal numbers with precision (1 or 2 decimal places)

    5. CULTURAL ADAPTATION NOTES:
       - Sleep patterns vary by culture - adapt language appropriately
       - Time formats may need localization (12/24 hour)
       - Consider local sleep terminology and health concepts
       - Maintain respect for different work schedules (shift workers, etc.)

    6. CHARACTER LIMITS (IMPORTANT FOR UI):
       - Button text: Maximum 25 characters
       - Notification titles: Maximum 50 characters
       - Toast messages: Maximum 80 characters
       - Error messages: Clear and concise, under 100 characters

    7. PERFORMANCE TERMINOLOGY:
       - "Native engine" = C++ high-performance algorithms
       - "Real-time" = instantaneous processing
       - "Microsecond precision" = extremely fast processing
       - These terms should convey speed and efficiency

    ========================================================================
    -->

